Under Satya Nadella, Microsoft has reclaimed its crown as the world’s most valuable listed company. What can other firms learn from its reboot? Also, Reshma Shetty, cofounder of Gingko Bioworks, explains the potential of synthetic biology to harness—and transform—the power of nature. And, British ethicists put police use of artificial intelligence on trial. Alok Jha hosts. Runtime: 18 min    Listen on: Apple Podcasts | Spotify | Google | Stitcher | TuneIn